1 (4) The individual drives or attempts to drive a commercial motor vehicle
2 while the alcohol concentration of the person’s blood or breath is 0.04 or greater; [or]
3 (5) THE INDIVIDUAL, WHILE HOLDING A COMMERCIAL
4 INSTRUCTIONAL PERMIT OR COMMERCIAL DRIVER’S LICENSE, DRIVES OR
5 ATTEMPTS TO DRIVE ANY MOTOR VEHICLE WHILE THE ALCOHOL CONCENTRATION
6 OF THE PERSON’S BLOOD OR BREATH IS 0.08 OR GREATER; OR
7 [(5)] (6) The individual drives a commercial motor vehicle when, as a
8 result of prior violations committed while driving a commercial motor vehicle, the driver’s
9 commercial instructional permit or commercial driver’s license is revoked, suspended, or
10 canceled or the driver is disqualified from driving a commercial motor vehicle.
11 (b) If any of the offenses in subsection (a) of this section occurred while
12 transporting a hazardous material required to be placarded, the Administration shall
13 disqualify the individual for a period of 3 years.
14 (c) The Administration shall disqualify any person from driving a commercial
15 motor vehicle for life for 2 or more violations of any of the offenses specified in subsection
16 (a) or (b) of this section, or any combination of those offenses, arising from 2 or more
17 separate incidents.
18 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
19 October 1, 2025.
